In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims July 20 through July 26, 2014, as Captive Nations Week. He reflects on the progress made in the fight for freedom during the Cold War, but acknowledges that there are still many people around the world who are oppressed and deprived of basic human rights. He expresses America's support for those seeking true democracy, prosperity, and security. The President calls upon the people of the United States to reaffirm their commitment to freedom, dignity, and opportunity for all.